JOHANNESBURG –SABC deputy chairperson Leah Khumalo is the latest member of the board to resign. The Presidency said on Friday that President Jacob Zuma had received and accepted Khumalo's resignation. “President Jacob Zuma has received and accepted the resignation of Ms Leah Thabisile Khumalo as a member and Deputy Chairperson of the Board of the South African Broadcasting Corporation, with immediate effect,” the presidency said. WATCH: ANC calls for inquiry into fitness of SABC board “The President has thanked Ms Khumalo for her contribution during her tenure at the SABC and wished her well in all her future endeavours.” Two other SABC board members recently resigned. Krish Naidoo and Vusi Mavuso resigned when the SABC board members appeared before the parliamentary communications portfolio committee in Parliament. eNCA